Twelve people were killed and multiple others were injured when a mini-bus taxi, truck and a bakkie were involved in a collision on the R33 in Greytown, at the turnoff to Wartburg (R614 ), on Tuesday,  at 7.21am. Shawn Herbst, Media Liaison Officer for Netcare 911 said that at 7.21am on Tuesday morning paramedics responded to reports of a collision on the R33 in Greytown. “A mini-bus taxi, truck and a bakkie were involved in a collision. Medics assessed the scene and found that twelve people had sadly lost their lives while multiple others had sustained moderate to serious injuries, ” said Herbst. Herbst said that all the patients were transported by various ambulance services to nearby hospitals. The road was closed in both directions. Police is investigating the cause of the accident.